    Reactivity Auto Calculation Rules

    Relative Wheal = Actual Wheal - Negative Control Wheal
    Prick scale
    • Relative Wheal = 0mm
      Reactivity = 0
    • 0mm < Relative Wheal < 3mm
      Reactivity = 1
    • 3mm ≤ Relative Wheal ≤ 7mm
      Reactivity = 2
    • 7mm < Relative Wheal ≤ 10mm
      Reactivity = 3
    • Relative Wheal > 10mm
      Reactivity = 4
    Intradermal scale
    • Relative Wheal = 0mm
      Reactivity = 0
    • 2mm ≤ Relative Wheal ≤ 4mm
      Reactivity = 1
    • 4mm < Relative Wheal ≤ 8mm
      Reactivity = 2
    • 8mm < Relative Wheal ≤ 10mm
      Reactivity = 3
    • Relative Wheal > 10mm
      Reactivity = 4

    Food Allergy Auto Calculation Rules

    Relative Wheal = Actual Wheal - Negative Control Wheal
    Risk Assessment
    • NO Symptom and Relative Wheal < 7mm
      Risk = Low
    • NO Symptom and Relative Wheal ≥ 7mm
      Risk = Moderate
    • HAS Symptom and Relative Wheal < 3mm
      Risk = Moderate
    • HAS Symptom and Relative Wheal ≥ 3mm
      Risk = High
    • NO Symptom and Relative Wheal ≥ 10mm
      Risk = High
    Decision
    • Risk = Low
      No choice
    • Risk = Moderate
      AVOID and OFC
    • Risk = High
      AVOID

    Expiration time
    Please enter the expiration time for each vial concentration. The expiration date for your mixed vaccine vials is automatically based on these values. Changing the values won't effect the mixed vaccine in the past.

    Yellow 1:1010 μg/mL

    Risk Assessment & Decision Auto Calculation Setting
    The Risk Assessment value and Decision will be automatically calculated basing on Wheal value and Symptoms based on these rules if you choose the option in while doing Food Test Interpretation.
    Risk Auto Calculation Rules
    Input value of Rule#1 and Rule#2 need to be the same. Input value of Rule#3 and Rule#4 need to be the same.
    1. Risk = Low
    when
    NO Symptom
    and
    Relative Wheal
    <
    2. Risk = Moderate
    when
    NO Symptom
    and
    Relative Wheal
    ≥
    3. Risk = Moderate
    when
    HAS Symptom
    and
    Relative Wheal
    <
    4. Risk = High
    when
    HAS Symptom
    and
    Relative Wheal
    ≥
    5. Risk = High
    when
    NO Symptom
    and
    Relative Wheal
    ≥
    *Relative wheal = Absolute Wheal - Negative control Wheal

    Continue to consume
    when
    Risk = Low
    AVOID and OFC
    when
    Risk = Moderate
    AVOID
    when
    Risk = High
